When you first enter the Section Editor with a Standard Assembly you will be presented with the following sidebar view.
image2064.gif
You can select any of the four Sides presented in the Side Selector. By selecting either of the Ends represented by the Side selector you will receive the following options:
image2072.gif
End Type -  You can define the Ends Type. There are eleven options here:
End Type -  You can define the Ends Type. There are eleven options here:
End Type -  You can define the Ends Type. There are eleven options here:

Automatic   -  When Automatic is selected as the End Type you give Solid control to determine what the End type is based on it’s condition. Basically this means it follows the logic of Unfinished End when against a Wall or other Assembly or Finished end when the End is exposed. 
 
 
 Unfinished   -  Changes the End type to an  Unfinished End  following its Properties as defined in whichever Construction Method that is active. This is an  Override  to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 Finished   -  Changes the End type to a  Finished End  following its Properties as defined in whichever Construction Method that is active. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 Applied Finished End   -  Changes the End type to an  Applied Finished End  following its Properties as defined in whichever Construction Method that is active. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 Applied Door   -  Changes the End type to an  Applied Door Finished End  following its Properties as defined in whichever Construction Method that is active, utilizing the selected Door Style for the Classes assigned End Panel. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 Panelized   -  Changes the End type to a  Panelized Finished End  following its Properties as defined in whichever Construction Method that is active, utilizing the selected Door Style for the Classes assigned End Panel. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 Extended –  Changes the End type to an  Extended Unfinished End  following its Properties as defined in whichever Construction Method that is active. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 Return   -  Changes the End type to a  Return Unfinished End  following its Properties as defined in whichever Construction Method that is active. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 Filler   -  Changes the End Type to Filler. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 Skin -  Changes the End Type to Skin. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog. 
 
 
 No End   -  Changes the End Type to No End. This is an Override to Solid’s "Automatic" End Type and will stick with the Assembly under all conditions, even when Saved into your Assembly Catalog.
